Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni has sworn-in six Permanent Secretaries in the state. The newly sworn-in permanent secretaries are Bashir Abubakar Sadiq, Abba Gana Mohammed Anas, Adamu Tela Zimbo, Alhaji Bukar Kilo, Isyaka Alhaji Lawan and Shuaibu Ibrahim Amshi, respectively. Governor Buni while congratulating them, said their appointment is best on merit, qualification, and individual competence for the office of permanent secretary in the service of the state. Buni who spoke at the swearing in ceremony, Monday inside Banquet hall of the Government House Damaturu noted that the events marked new chapter in their carrier. He further revealed that government and good people of  yobe state are expecting to justify this elevation through hard work, efficiency and increase productivity. “This administration places much emphases  on accountability, transparency and conformity in conducting government affairs. “I urge you to be guided by the code of ethics and conduct your selves in conformity of oaths of allegiance and office your sworn to uphold,” he said.